<https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20039402>
        rdf:type               obo:T4FS_0000113;
        datacite:IsPartOf      <https://zenodo.org/communities/nfdi4bioimage/>;
        datacite:IsVersionOf   <https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20039401>;
        datacite:Issued        "2026-05-05"^^xs:date;
        datacite:Updated       "2026-05-06"^^xs:date;
        datacite:creator       orcid:0000-0003-2237-1147;
        datacite:description   "This presentation was developed by NFDI4BIOIMAGE and held online as part of the CRC 1551 Data Week on 05. May 2026.\n\nIt provides a general introduction to research data management (RDM) and public data deposition and highlights their specific relevance in research.\n\nFurthermore, it introduces OMERO as a platform for structured data storage, metadata management, and collaborative access and introduces repositories for imaging data.\n\nThe slides are intended for educational use and may serve as a resource for teaching and training in research data management within the life sciences.\n\nWe acknowledge funding by the Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG, German Research Foundation) under the National Research Data Infrastructure – NFDI 46/1 – 501864659.";
        datacite:resourceType  "Presentation";
        datacite:right         "None" , "Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International";
        datacite:subject       "public data deposition" , "research data management" , "bioimaging" , "OMERO";
        datacite:title         "From Microscope to Repository: Managing Image Data with OMERO" .

<https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20024684>
        rdf:type               obo:T4FS_0000113;
        datacite:IsPartOf      <https://zenodo.org/communities/ome/> , <https://zenodo.org/communities/nfdi4bioimage/>;
        datacite:IsVersionOf   <https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20024683>;
        datacite:Issued        "2026-05-04"^^xs:date , "2026-04-28"^^xs:date;
        datacite:Updated       "2026-05-27"^^xs:date;
        datacite:creator       orcid:0009-0002-1826-7099;
        datacite:description   "This publication contains the Poster and accompanying Lightning Talk about the \"enriched\" OMERO held at the OME Community Meeting 2026 in Düsseldorf\n\nAbstract: \n\nFollowing the example of Fiji, NFDI4Bioimage provides a public OMERO instance \"with batteries included\".\n\nFrom a variety of different plugins and scripts to a diverse spectrum of sample image data, the \"enriched\" OMERO will allow users and developers to test plugins, configurations, endpoints and provide sample image data for all kinds of different workflows.\n\nThe vision is to have an OMERO instance \"enriched\" with as many features as possible to give the bioimaging community a platform to test workflows and processes that they otherwise might not be able to implement that quickly on their own instance, if they even have one.\n\nWe acknowledge funding by the Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG, German Research Foundation) under the National Research Data Infrastructure – NFDI 46/1 – 501864659.";
        datacite:resourceType  "Poster";
        datacite:right         "None" , "Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International";
        datacite:subject       "OME Community Meeting 2026" , "NFDI4Bioimage" , "OMERO";
        datacite:title         "[OME2026] Poster and Lightning Talk for \"enriched\" OMERO from the OME Community Meeting 2026" .

<https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19949157>
        rdf:type               obo:T4FS_0000113;
        datacite:Accepted      "2026-04-29"^^xs:date;
