        datacite:Updated       "2026-02-22"^^xs:date;
        datacite:creator       orcid:0000-0001-5949-2327;
        datacite:description   "In  this slide deck we dive into generative artificial intelligence in particular used for code generation and see how it impacts Bio-Image Data Science. We learn about benchmarking large language models for data analysis code generation, and how to use them practically in our work.";
        datacite:resourceType  "Presentation";
        datacite:right         "None" , "Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International";
        datacite:title         "How Generative Artificial Intelligence impacts Bio-Image Data Science" .

<https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18712011>
        rdf:type               obo:T4FS_0000113;
        datacite:IsPartOf      <https://zenodo.org/communities/nfdi4bioimage/>;
        datacite:IsVersionOf   <https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18712010>;
        datacite:Issued        "2026-02-28"^^xs:date;
        datacite:Updated       "2026-04-20"^^xs:date;
        datacite:contributor   orcid:0000-0002-9501-6165 , orcid:0000-0002-8367-5163;
        datacite:creator       orcid:0000-0001-6676-8440 , orcid:0000-0002-3209-1221;
        datacite:description   "A Python-based stitching script for individual tiles obtained with an automated imaging platform that combines the Vertebrate Automated Screening Technology (VAST) BioImager system (Union Biometrica), the Large Particle (LP) Sampler (Union Biometrica), and the Zeiss Cell Observer Spinning Disk Confocal Microscopic System (SDCM) (Early et al., 2018). The Lyons Lab (https://www.lyons-lab.com/) designed the system as a screening tool for automated, high-resolution, in vivo imaging of 2–5-day-old zebrafish larvae. Two datasets are available to test the script, along with the final stitched files for comparison. ";
        datacite:resourceType  "Technical note";
        datacite:right         "None" , "Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International";
        datacite:title         "Workflow and Example Dataset for Python-Based Stitching of Confocal Zebrafish Images from VAST BioImager-Based Screening" .

